⚡ SPI Communication

| Pin | Function |
| --- | -------- |
| 10  | SS       |
| 11  | MOSI     |
| 12  | MISO     |
| 13  | SCK      |

Pin Definitions


MOSI = Master Out Slave In
MISO = Master In Slave Out
SCK  = Serial Clock
SS   = Slave Select


Used for:

* SD Card modules
* OLED displays
* TFT displays
* High-speed sensors



🔗 I²C Communication

| Pin | Function |
| --- | -------- |
| A4  | SDA      |
| A5  | SCL      |

Pin Definitions


SDA = Serial Data
SCL = Serial Clock


Used for:

* OLED displays
* RTC modules
* EEPROM chips
* Environmental sensors

Only two wires are required regardless of the number of connected devices.



💡 Built-in LED

Arduino Uno includes an onboard LED connected to pin 13.
:
digitalWrite(13, HIGH);


Turns the built-in LED ON.
:
digitalWrite(13, LOW);


Turns the built-in LED OFF.

Useful for testing and debugging programs.

